In the thickest of the fight, One by one we drop from sight. Fierce the combat, right with wrong, . On, ye valiant, swell our throng : Riches, honor, place and fame Are but rattles round one's name; Life is earnest, life is grand, \Vhen for truth and God we stand. Times are changing: gold is god; Schools must pander to its nod. Classic culture; what a waste; Lighter learning suits the taste; Wealth for show, and greed for gain, Skill in tricks: such graces reign.
